267
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:46,435
Yes, she is here,
and she is waiting for you!

268
00:20:46,835 --> 00:20:49,554
She's not waiting for me,
she's waiting for you.

269
00:20:50,195 --> 00:20:51,423
Are you coming?

270
00:20:52,275 --> 00:20:53,867
No! I'm playing cards!

271
00:20:55,635 --> 00:20:57,034
You're not coming?

272
00:20:59,555 --> 00:21:01,034
Get over here, Dalby!

273
00:21:14,356 --> 00:21:16,950
Look, I'm sorry about
the misunderstanding.

274
00:21:18,756 --> 00:21:21,224
Joel, be a courageous person.
Open the door!

275
00:21:21,316 --> 00:21:23,546
That way, you see, I can call a cab.

276
00:21:24,596 --> 00:21:26,188
Again, I'm really sorry.

277
00:21:26,676 --> 00:21:30,351
As long as we come to an arrangement,
I'm in no mood for complaining.

278
00:21:30,436 --> 00:21:32,996
I mean, when you put
your good money down...

279
00:21:33,076 --> 00:21:36,193
...you gotta get what you wanted
in the first place. Know what I mean?

280
00:21:36,276 --> 00:21:39,314
When you buy a TV,
you don't buy Sony if you want RCA.

281
00:21:40,837 --> 00:21:43,226
I know we could get along
real well. But, hey!

282
00:21:43,317 --> 00:21:45,592
It's your hard-earned money, right?

283
00:21:46,357 --> 00:21:49,633
This way, we make an arrangement
and everyone is satisfied.

284
00:21:49,957 --> 00:21:51,231
You had carfare.

285
00:21:51,317 --> 00:21:54,150
A long ride. I don't ever come out this far.

286
00:21:55,317 --> 00:21:56,352
And your time.

287
00:21:56,437 --> 00:21:59,554
My time, my effort,
my infinite patience and understanding.

288
00:21:59,637 --> 00:22:00,592
Thank you.

289
00:22:00,677 --> 00:22:01,632
$75.

290
00:22:03,557 --> 00:22:04,512
Fair enough.

291
00:22:04,597 --> 00:22:06,986
Joel, I'm going to give you a number.

292
00:22:07,717 --> 00:22:09,276
You ask for Lana.

293
00:22:10,158 --> 00:22:12,069
- It's what you want.
- Thank you.

294
00:22:14,198 --> 00:22:16,712
It's what every white boy
off the lake wants.

295
00:22:47,319 --> 00:22:49,879
All right, Goodson,
we know you're in there!

296
00:22:50,439 --> 00:22:51,554
What's that?

297
00:22:52,679 --> 00:22:54,510
I think someone's out there.

298
00:23:00,999 --> 00:23:02,910
Joel, the house is surrounded.

299
00:23:04,119 --> 00:23:06,679
Do exactly as we say,
and no one gets hurt.

300
00:23:07,479 --> 00:23:08,435
Oh, shit!

301
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:12,911
Get off the babysitter! Put on your
pants, and come out with your hands up!

302
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:21,711
Please, Joel, do as they say!

303
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:24,998
Get off the babysitter!

304
00:23:25,080 --> 00:23:27,310
Don't throw your life away like this.

305
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:33,951
Listen, you goddamn punk, you'll never
have a future! Not if I can help it!

306
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,911
You got that? No future!

307
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,995
Who is that?

308
00:23:39,401 --> 00:23:40,436
My father!

309
00:24:35,162 --> 00:24:36,561
Hello? Lana?

310
00:24:37,883 --> 00:24:38,679
Yes?

311
00:24:40,203 --> 00:24:40,999
Hi.

312
00:24:53,723 --> 00:24:56,112
I'm a nice guy,
and I'd like to meet you tonight.

313
00:24:56,203 --> 00:24:57,716
Fine. Where are you?

314
00:25:00,683 --> 00:25:02,036
Where do you live?

315
00:25:05,963 --> 00:25:06,918
Glencoe.

316
00:25:07,964 --> 00:25:09,283
What's your name?

317
00:25:14,764 --> 00:25:15,674
Ralph.

318
00:25:16,764 --> 00:25:18,880
Ralph, can I have the address?

319
00:25:25,244 --> 00:25:26,154
345...

320
00:25:28,164 --> 00:25:29,233
...Remson.

321
00:25:30,524 --> 00:25:31,434
Ralph?

322
00:25:34,284 --> 00:25:35,763
I'll see you tonight.

323
00:27:12,248 --> 00:27:14,159
Are you ready for me, Ralph?

324
00:29:08,372 --> 00:29:11,444
This is a beautiful place, Ralph.
Is it all yours?

325
00:29:12,212 --> 00:29:13,850
It's my folks', actually.

326
00:29:14,772 --> 00:29:16,683
Do you know what it's worth?

327
00:29:18,812 --> 00:29:20,006
A lot, probably.

328
00:29:20,092 --> 00:29:21,684
Oh, yeah! Real estate?

329
00:29:22,012 --> 00:29:23,240
It's fabulous!

330
00:29:24,052 --> 00:29:26,646
Look, Lana... my name really isn't Ralph.

331
00:29:30,492 --> 00:29:31,766
It's Joel.

332
00:29:33,052 --> 00:29:34,724
I need $300... Joel.

333
00:29:37,813 --> 00:29:38,882
You're kidding?

334
00:29:38,973 --> 00:29:40,486
No, I don't believe I am.

335
00:29:40,573 --> 00:29:42,165
Can I send it to you?

336
00:29:45,053 --> 00:29:46,930
Can you send it to me, Joel?

337
00:29:47,453 --> 00:29:50,331
I just don't have that much here
in the house.

338
00:29:51,133 --> 00:29:52,885
How much do you have?

339
00:29:53,813 --> 00:29:55,371
- I have $50.
- $50?

340
00:29:56,653 --> 00:29:58,723
What are we going to do about this?

341
00:30:04,693 --> 00:30:06,251
I have a bond at the bank I could cash...

342
00:30:06,333 --> 00:30:08,404
I'm not good at waiting for people.

343
00:30:09,814 --> 00:30:11,008
I'll be quick.

344
00:30:11,454 --> 00:30:12,728
Give it a try.

345
00:30:50,975 --> 00:30:52,010
I'm back!

346
00:31:04,775 --> 00:31:06,094
I'm here for you.

347
00:31:25,976 --> 00:31:28,046
How could she? It's so stupid!

348
00:31:28,376 --> 00:31:29,729
Tell your mother it broke!

349
00:31:29,816 --> 00:31:32,410
That egg is worth a lot more than $300!

350
00:31:33,336 --> 00:31:34,974
What are you going to do?

351
00:31:35,576 --> 00:31:37,772
I'm gonna get it back,
is what I'm gonna do.

352
00:31:37,857 --> 00:31:38,573
Are you going to help?

353
00:31:38,657 --> 00:31:39,772
Sure. When?

354
00:31:41,497 --> 00:31:42,532
Right now!

355
00:31:42,777 --> 00:31:45,974
I can't do it right now!
I have a trig. Mid-term tomorrow!

356
00:31:46,497 --> 00:31:47,850
Hey, "Mr. What-The-Fuck"...

357
00:31:47,937 --> 00:31:50,246
...what about "exploring
the dark side" and all that?

358
00:31:50,337 --> 00:31:52,055
Or was that just bullshit?

359
00:31:52,537 --> 00:31:54,414
That was just bullshit, Joel.

360
00:31:56,097 --> 00:31:58,292
I'm surprised you listened to me.

361
00:32:03,777 --> 00:32:05,051
Are you coming?

362
00:32:13,498 --> 00:32:15,887
How can you even tell if she'll be here?

363
00:32:17,058 --> 00:32:19,697
I called Jackie and she said to try here.

364
00:32:21,178 --> 00:32:24,727
Great idea. Where else could
we get a hot chocolate for $4?

365
00:32:26,938 --> 00:32:28,007
She's here!

366
00:32:29,418 --> 00:32:30,533
Where?

367
00:32:31,578 --> 00:32:33,773
The blue dress... those legs...

368
00:32:35,458 --> 00:32:36,573
That's her.

369
00:32:36,698 --> 00:32:38,212
She's fantastic!

370
00:32:47,779 --> 00:32:49,451
She's looking right at us!

371
00:32:58,019 --> 00:32:59,498
She knows we're here.

372
00:33:09,340 --> 00:33:10,614
That's it?

373
00:33:11,540 --> 00:33:12,859
That's it, Joel?

374
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:18,698
I can't believe we came
all the way here for that!

375
00:33:20,740 --> 00:33:22,731
At least she knows we're on to her, Miles.

376
00:33:22,820 --> 00:33:24,617
Yeah, she must be terrified.

377
00:33:24,700 --> 00:33:25,735
Joel!

378
00:33:29,380 --> 00:33:30,699
Is this your car?

379
00:33:31,620 --> 00:33:32,530
Maybe.

380
00:33:34,460 --> 00:33:36,098
Could we talk a minute?

381
00:33:36,540 --> 00:33:37,576
Okay.

382
00:33:38,421 --> 00:33:39,490
Let's talk!

383
00:33:39,901 --> 00:33:42,495
Okay. In the car, all right? It's freezing.

384
00:33:53,701 --> 00:33:55,339
Will you do me a favor?

385
00:33:56,421 --> 00:33:58,252
You want me to do you a favor?

386
00:33:58,341 --> 00:33:59,569
I just need a lift.

387
00:33:59,661 --> 00:34:01,333
Look, I want my egg back!

388
00:34:04,221 --> 00:34:05,336
Get out of the car!

389
00:34:05,421 --> 00:34:06,695
Joel, better get moving.

390
00:34:06,781 --> 00:34:08,135
I want my egg back!

391
00:34:08,222 --> 00:34:09,974
You got it, all right? Just start driving!

392
00:34:10,062 --> 00:34:10,892
When?

393
00:34:11,422 --> 00:34:12,855
- Now!
- Open the door!

394
00:34:13,582 --> 00:34:14,697
When do I get it back?

395
00:34:14,782 --> 00:34:15,931
Start driving!

396
00:34:16,022 --> 00:34:18,536
Open the door!
Are you going to open the door?

397
00:34:18,622 --> 00:34:19,737
Hey, buster!

398
00:34:20,182 --> 00:34:20,978
Fuck! Will you just...

399
00:34:21,062 --> 00:34:23,018
- Get off the car!
- Just start driving!

400
00:34:23,102 --> 00:34:24,501
Start driving, now!

401
00:34:25,982 --> 00:34:28,018
Why don't you start the car, Joel?

402
00:34:29,022 --> 00:34:30,375
Fuck! Get out of here!

403
00:34:30,462 --> 00:34:32,373
Start the goddamn car, Joel!

404
00:34:32,702 --> 00:34:34,135
Lana, open the door.

405
00:34:36,222 --> 00:34:37,941
Where are you going? Lana!

406
00:34:38,143 --> 00:34:39,861
Get out, or I'll kill you!

407
00:34:50,783 --> 00:34:52,136
Who was that guy?

408
00:34:52,383 --> 00:34:53,657
My manager.

409
00:34:54,263 --> 00:34:56,333
He gets a little crazy sometimes.

410
00:34:57,743 --> 00:34:59,415
This is my friend, Miles.

411
00:35:01,663 --> 00:35:03,574
Do you like excitement, Miles?

412
00:35:03,903 --> 00:35:04,858
Love it.

413
00:35:21,864 --> 00:35:23,775
Okay, where do you want to go?

414
00:35:24,544 --> 00:35:27,695
I don't know, Joel.
I haven't given it a lot of thought.

415
00:35:27,784 --> 00:35:28,978
Tell me this:

416
00:35:29,184 --> 00:35:31,220
Am I going in the right direction?

417
00:35:33,184 --> 00:35:34,822
Oh, shit! Here he comes!

418
00:35:35,184 --> 00:35:36,412
Here who comes?

419
00:35:37,024 --> 00:35:38,538
That manager guy?

420
00:35:42,465 --> 00:35:43,534
Hey, Guido!

421
00:35:43,945 --> 00:35:45,424
Big man, Guido!

422
00:35:46,465 --> 00:35:47,864
Big man with a gun!

423
00:35:48,065 --> 00:35:49,259
What are you going to do?

424
00:35:49,345 --> 00:35:50,858
Shoot us all? Stupid!

425
00:35:55,265 --> 00:35:56,823
This guy Guido...

426
00:35:57,345 --> 00:35:59,415
...he's a "manager"?
- That's right.

427
00:36:00,225 --> 00:36:01,294
Or a pimp?

428
00:36:01,505 --> 00:36:03,097
Now, that's quick, Joel.

429
00:36:03,505 --> 00:36:06,224
Have you always been this quick,
or is this something new?

430
00:36:06,305 --> 00:36:07,819
I don't believe this!

431
00:36:07,906 --> 00:36:09,464
I have a trig. Mid-term tomorrow...

432
00:36:09,546 --> 00:36:12,344
...and I'm being chased by Guido,
The Killer Pimp!

433
00:36:36,706 --> 00:36:37,617
Miles?

434
00:36:39,107 --> 00:36:40,096
I think I can take him.

435
00:36:40,187 --> 00:36:41,825
What are you talking...

436
00:37:10,828 --> 00:37:12,659
I'm really not enjoying this.

437
00:37:32,068 --> 00:37:33,979
I think I'm going to throw up.

438
00:37:42,989 --> 00:37:45,503
I think I'm going to throw up on you, Joel!

439
00:38:06,629 --> 00:38:07,904
Porsche...

440
00:38:08,110 --> 00:38:09,782
...there is no substitute.

441
00:38:12,630 --> 00:38:13,699
Fuck you.

442
00:38:18,110 --> 00:38:19,907
Hi, dear. It's Mother.

443
00:38:20,030 --> 00:38:21,258
How are you?

444
00:38:21,350 --> 00:38:23,705
Just checking in to say hello,
see how you're doing...

445
00:38:23,790 --> 00:38:26,065
...and give you our flight information.

446
00:38:27,790 --> 00:38:30,384
Wait a minute. Let me write this down.

447
00:38:31,750 --> 00:38:34,218
Saturday, United, Flight 162 at 3:30.

448
00:38:36,270 --> 00:38:40,025
That's right. How's everything else?
Do you have enough money?

449
00:38:41,031 --> 00:38:43,909
It never seems to go as far
as you think it will.

450
00:38:45,751 --> 00:38:47,104
Yes, I know.

451
00:38:47,631 --> 00:38:49,030
I'm learning, Mom.

452
00:38:50,991 --> 00:38:52,310
How is Aunt Tudi?

453
00:38:56,791 --> 00:38:57,940
I will.

454
00:38:59,151 --> 00:39:00,550
See you then, bye.

455
00:39:02,951 --> 00:39:04,225
Your folks?

456
00:39:05,511 --> 00:39:06,944
So, how are they?

457
00:39:07,271 --> 00:39:08,910
Oh, they're just great.

458
00:39:09,032 --> 00:39:10,465
How about Aunt Tudi?

459
00:39:10,632 --> 00:39:13,146
Her hip is much better.
She sends her love.

460
00:39:18,512 --> 00:39:20,468
You were telling me about Guido.

461
00:39:20,792 --> 00:39:21,986
I quit Guido.

462
00:39:24,552 --> 00:39:25,587
How come?

463
00:39:30,192 --> 00:39:31,864
He thought he owned me.

464
00:39:33,352 --> 00:39:34,580
Nobody owns me.

465
00:39:38,353 --> 00:39:41,663
The problem is, I owe him for clothes
and hospital bills.

466
00:39:41,913 --> 00:39:43,585
You were in the hospital?

467
00:39:45,033 --> 00:39:46,432
I had this...

468
00:39:47,313 --> 00:39:48,507
...pain in my chest.

469
00:39:48,593 --> 00:39:50,709
I thought it was a heart condition.

470
00:39:52,593 --> 00:39:53,708
What was it?

471
00:39:53,993 --> 00:39:55,631
The doctor said nerves.

472
00:39:56,073 --> 00:39:57,472
Nice service.

473
00:39:58,353 --> 00:39:59,581
Reed & Barton.

474
00:40:02,353 --> 00:40:04,742
Thank you for breakfast. It was good.

475
00:40:06,993 --> 00:40:08,632
I'm going to school now.

476
00:40:13,954 --> 00:40:15,831
I'll have to ask you to leave.

477
00:40:19,394 --> 00:40:20,463
I'm sorry.

478
00:40:21,554 --> 00:40:23,067
You won't let me stay?

479
00:40:24,274 --> 00:40:26,185
No, I have to go to school.

480
00:40:30,514 --> 00:40:32,072
I'm really sorry.

481
00:40:36,274 --> 00:40:37,469
No, I'm sorry.

482
00:40:42,875 --> 00:40:44,274
I'll be right back.

483
00:40:47,555 --> 00:40:49,386
You guys go ahead without me.

484
00:40:50,075 --> 00:40:51,303
She's still here?

485
00:40:51,395 --> 00:40:52,714
She won't leave.

486
00:40:56,195 --> 00:40:57,514
She won't leave.

487
00:41:02,755 --> 00:41:04,188
Lana, look...

488
00:41:05,235 --> 00:41:07,989
...I just want my egg back.
I want my house back.

489
00:41:09,076 --> 00:41:10,794
I have a lot of work to do.

490
00:41:12,996 --> 00:41:15,112
Did you have a good time last night?

491
00:41:18,516 --> 00:41:20,666
You mean when we got back here?

492
00:41:21,636 --> 00:41:23,467
I think you know what I mean.

493
00:41:29,716 --> 00:41:31,354
I had a great time.

494
00:41:34,596 --> 00:41:36,985
Don't tell me I owe you another $300.

495
00:41:39,037 --> 00:41:40,948
Did I say you owe me anything?

496
00:41:43,477 --> 00:41:44,114
No, you didn't.

497
00:41:44,197 --> 00:41:46,916
I don't remember saying
you owe me anything.

498
00:41:52,597 --> 00:41:54,508
What about my mother's egg?

499
00:41:55,237 --> 00:41:58,434
You're the one who's going to college,
you figure it out.

500
00:42:02,557 --> 00:42:04,195
How much time do you need?

501
00:42:04,277 --> 00:42:06,871
I need long enough
to make a few phone calls.

502
00:42:07,157 --> 00:42:09,718
I have to figure out how
to get my stuff back.

503
00:42:09,798 --> 00:42:12,949
Guido has probably locked me
out of the apartment by now.

504
00:42:13,318 --> 00:42:14,387
All right!

505
00:42:16,198 --> 00:42:17,950
But will you do me a favor?

506
00:42:18,438 --> 00:42:19,757
Anything, cookie.

507
00:42:21,758 --> 00:42:23,396
Don't steal anything!

508
00:42:26,078 --> 00:42:28,831
If I come back here,
and find anything missing...

509
00:42:29,958 --> 00:42:32,870
...l'm going straight to the police.
I'm not joking!

510
00:42:33,798 --> 00:42:36,187
Joel, go to school. Go learn something.

511
00:42:50,599 --> 00:42:52,430
May I see your pass, please!

512
00:42:54,199 --> 00:42:57,396
I'm sure you've all read
chapters six through eight...

513
00:42:57,799 --> 00:43:00,188
...so here's a little pop quiz to confirm it.

514
00:43:00,279 --> 00:43:02,839
Will you put your books on the floor,
please?

515
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:25,988
You didn't tell anyone, did you?

516
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:27,399
No. Glenn knows.

517
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:29,069
What about Barry?

518
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:30,388
He knows, too.

519
00:43:30,680 --> 00:43:32,238
Don't tell anyone!

520
00:43:32,680 --> 00:43:34,033
I won't! I won't!

521
00:43:43,401 --> 00:43:46,598
Lab reports should be on my desk
by tomorrow afternoon.

522
00:43:47,561 --> 00:43:49,756
I won't accept any that aren't typed.

523
00:44:04,521 --> 00:44:06,671
Term papers are due on Friday.

524
00:44:06,761 --> 00:44:09,322
They count for 50%
of this semester's grades.

525
00:44:11,482 --> 00:44:12,437
Damn it!

526
00:44:21,802 --> 00:44:22,917
Hey, Miles, what's going on?

527
00:44:23,002 --> 00:44:24,515
I'm waiting for Glenn.

528
00:44:24,762 --> 00:44:25,990
Glenn? Where is he?

529
00:44:26,082 --> 00:44:27,037
Inside.

530
00:44:27,802 --> 00:44:28,996
In the house?

531
00:44:29,082 --> 00:44:30,595
He wanted to meet her!

532
00:44:32,802 --> 00:44:33,791
What are you doing?

533
00:44:33,882 --> 00:44:34,837
I was inside.

534
00:44:34,922 --> 00:44:36,196
I can see that.

535
00:44:39,083 --> 00:44:40,596
You're home now.

536
00:44:41,003 --> 00:44:42,834
Yeah, I live here, remember?

537
