1070
01:28:47,171 --> 01:28:48,206
No...

1071
01:28:48,971 --> 01:28:50,404
...I don't think so.

1072
01:28:51,171 --> 01:28:54,243
I just got off the telephone
with Bill Rutherford.

1073
01:28:57,011 --> 01:28:59,650
Apparently, you two had quite a meeting.

1074
01:29:04,451 --> 01:29:06,682
"Princeton can use a guy like Joel."

1075
01:29:08,692 --> 01:29:09,568
What?

1076
01:29:10,052 --> 01:29:12,441
"Princeton can use a guy like Joel."

1077
01:29:13,892 --> 01:29:15,211
His exact words!

1078
01:29:17,332 --> 01:29:18,811
That's unbelievable!

1079
01:29:18,932 --> 01:29:20,650
You're as good as in!

1080
01:29:21,012 --> 01:29:22,650
I knew you could do it!

1081
01:29:22,772 --> 01:29:25,411
Haven't I been telling you,
sometimes you have to say:

1082
01:29:25,492 --> 01:29:27,801
"What the heck!" Take some chances.

1083
01:29:27,892 --> 01:29:29,245
You were so right.

1084
01:29:29,492 --> 01:29:31,164
You've made me very proud.

1085
01:29:37,013 --> 01:29:38,605
I was just thinking...

1086
01:29:39,813 --> 01:29:42,202
...where we might be ten years from now.

1087
01:29:44,693 --> 01:29:46,490
You know what I think?

1088
01:29:46,653 --> 01:29:48,928
I think we're both going to make it big!

1089
01:29:49,013 --> 01:29:51,243
I'm very optimistic! I mean it!

1090
01:29:55,493 --> 01:29:57,131
Can I ask you something?

1091
01:30:01,813 --> 01:30:03,724
Was our night together...

1092
01:30:06,614 --> 01:30:08,332
...just to set up...

1093
01:30:09,334 --> 01:30:10,733
...Vicki and Guido?

1094
01:30:19,854 --> 01:30:20,809
No.

1095
01:30:22,454 --> 01:30:24,285
You don't believe me, do you?

1096
01:30:26,454 --> 01:30:29,332
My name is Russell Bitterman.
I'm from Wheaton High School.

1097
01:30:29,414 --> 01:30:32,850
Our product is a paper-towel
holder that sells for $8.95.

1098
01:30:33,974 --> 01:30:36,569
We made a profit of $850 last semester.

1099
01:30:43,175 --> 01:30:45,052
I don't want you to get hurt.

1100
01:30:47,255 --> 01:30:51,009
My name is Evonne Williams.
We sell decorative planters for $7.

1101
01:30:52,455 --> 01:30:55,049
We made a profit of $500 last semester.

1102
01:30:58,135 --> 01:31:00,808
Guess we won't see each other for awhile.

1103
01:31:01,335 --> 01:31:02,290
I know.

1104
01:31:04,215 --> 01:31:05,808
Are you going straight home now?

1105
01:31:05,896 --> 01:31:07,295
I don't know. Why?

1106
01:31:07,736 --> 01:31:10,808
It might be nice if we spent
the evening together.

1107
01:31:12,216 --> 01:31:13,774
I'd really like that.

1108
01:31:15,096 --> 01:31:16,973
How much have you got on you?

1109
01:31:18,616 --> 01:31:20,095
How much have I got on me?

1110
01:31:20,176 --> 01:31:21,325
I've got $20.

1111
01:31:21,976 --> 01:31:23,091
$20, Lana?

1112
01:31:24,136 --> 01:31:26,206
What are we going to do about this?

1113
01:31:26,296 --> 01:31:29,015
- Can I send it to you?
- Can you send it to me?

1114
01:31:29,856 --> 01:31:31,687
'Cause I don't have that much here.

1115
01:31:31,776 --> 01:31:33,255
How about I write you a check?

1116
01:31:33,336 --> 01:31:36,647
Do you think I'd accept a check from you?
What am I, stupid?

1117
01:31:37,817 --> 01:31:39,489
I have a bond at the bank.

1118
01:31:41,017 --> 01:31:42,609
My name is Joel Goodson.

1119
01:31:43,577 --> 01:31:45,408
I deal in human fulfillment.

1120
01:31:46,457 --> 01:31:48,846
I grossed over $8,000 in one night.

1121
01:31:50,617 --> 01:31:52,608
The time of your life, huh, kid?

